The paper discusses a method for estimating the distributions of sources in a time series, which involves modeling the data as a hidden Markov model (HMM). This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), information theory (cs.IT), or social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the robustness of HMMs and proposes a non-stationary model for the data, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), which deals with the development and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are not as directly related to the paper's main topic.
